# Agents & skills in Cursor (Boardupscale)

Cursor does not run slash-commands like `/pipeline` natively. Treat the repo’s **agent definitions** as **role contracts**: open the file and follow its checklist when the task matches.

## Cursor skill: full delivery orchestrator (`.cursor/skills/`)

For **end-to-end** work — analysis → plan → implementation → tests → review (e.g. “audit Jira migration sync and fix gaps”, “master flow”, “full pipeline”) — apply the project skill **`boardupscale-master-delivery`**: read `.cursor/skills/boardupscale-master-delivery/SKILL.md` and follow it. It sequences Master + Pipeline + gates in a Cursor-native way (no separate “assign agent” runtime; you execute the playbook and pull in the right `.claude/agents/*.md` files per phase).

## Agent roster (`.claude/agents/`)

| Agent file | Use when |
|------------|----------|
| `master.md` | Large goals, sequencing, cross-cutting decisions |
| `pipeline.md` | Single deliverable through gates (design → impl → QA mental model) |
| `architect.md` | Module boundaries, DDD, events, scalability |
| `database.md` | Schema, Postgres, indexing, tenant columns |
| `migration.md` | Migration safety (rollback, nullable, indexes) |
| `backend.md` | NestJS, guards, DTOs, services |
| `frontend.md` | React/Vite web app, TanStack Query, Zustand |
| `worker.md` | BullMQ jobs, retries, idempotency |
| `realtime.md` | Socket.io, rooms, JWT handshake |
| `rbac.md` | Permissions, roles, org vs project scope |
| `search.md` | Elasticsearch, indexing pipeline |
| `github.md` | GitHub integration |
| `payments.md` | Billing (if touched) |
| `ai.md` | Embeddings / LLM features |
| `security.md` | Threat model, tenant bypass, OWASP |
| `qa.md` | Tests, coverage, E2E |
| `reviewer.md` | Final review, BLOCK/WARN/APPROVE style |
| `product.md` | PM tool parity, Jira/Linear behavior |
| `devops.md` | Docker, CI, deploy |
| `docs.md` | OpenAPI, ADRs |
| `master-jira-import.md` | Jira → Boardupscale migration orchestration |
| **`mcp-jira.md`** | **Jira + MCP expert:** use Atlassian MCP for discovery, REST/scripts for bulk, persist via import API + worker (not raw SQL) |

**How to invoke in Cursor:** e.g. *“Follow `.claude/agents/backend.md` for this Nest change”* or *“Run a product audit per `product.md` on this feature.”*

## Skills (`.claude/skills/`)

| Skill | Path | Purpose |
|-------|------|---------|
| Master | `.claude/skills/master/SKILL.md` | Top-level orchestration hint |
| Pipeline | `.claude/skills/pipeline/SKILL.md` | Single-task pipeline hint |
| MCP + Jira | `.claude/skills/mcp-jira/SKILL.md` | Jira MCP discovery + Boardupscale persistence path |

Use skills as **short delegation hints**; full behavior lives in the matching `agents/*.md` file.

## Gates (from `CLAUDE.md`)

For risky changes, mentally apply: **migration** (schema), **qa** (tests), **security** (auth/tenant), **reviewer** (ship/no-ship). Do not skip tenant tests for new org-scoped APIs.
